Acting national police commissioner Khomotso Phahlane has been suspended with immediate effect.Phahlane has been replaced by LtGen Joel Mothiba, formerly the divisional head of the SAPS management intervention unit.Phahlane s suspension comes in the wake of a probe into the personal affairs of Phahlane by the Independent Police Investigative Directorate (Ipid), which has been probing claims of corruption against him and also accused him of obstructing its work.Ipid alleged that Phahlane has been investigating its investigatorsNews of the suspension was released yesterday. Police Minister Fikile Mbalula, who announced the suspension at a briefing in Parliament yesterday, said he had advised President Jacob Zuma to suspend Phahlane.Mbalula will meet police management and generals today to inform them of the news.On Ipid s allegations against LtGen Phahlane, including that he had launched what has been called a North West team to act against it, Mbalula insisted that any form of criminality must be attended to.news@thenewage.co.za